#X text 366 565 HINT: We've had an example earlier before where we used keyboard tracking to set a ratio multiplier for the envelopes. You can expand on this idea and also have the keyboard tracking affect the the envelope time for the filter and/or amplitude. Not only that \, but you can also think of having the LFO speed higher for higher pitches! Do it as an excercize!, f 34;
